{
  "page": "Lord of Maidenpool",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Lord of Maidenpool</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> is a title held by the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Mooton\" title=\"House Mooton\">House Mooton</a>, the ruler of <a href=\"/index.php/Maidenpool\" title=\"Maidenpool\">Maidenpool</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\">\n<div style=\"position: relative; border: 1px solid lightgray\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Riverlands.png\" class=\"image\" title=\"The riverlands and the location of Maidenpool\"><img alt=\"The riverlands and the location of Maidenpool\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d0/The_Riverlands.png/300px-The_Riverlands.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"338\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d0/The_Riverlands.png/450px-The_Riverlands.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d0/The_Riverlands.png/600px-The_Riverlands.png 2x\" /></a><div style=\"position: absolute; z-index: 2; top: 72.2%; left: 90.6%; height: 0; width: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"><div style=\"position: relative; text-align: center; left: -5px; top: -5px; width: 10px; font-size: 10px;\"><img alt=\"The riverlands and the location of Maidenpool\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/10px-Red_pog.png\" title=\"Maidenpool\" width=\"10\" height=\"10\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/15px-Red_pog.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/20px-Red_pog.png 2x\" /></div><div style=\"font-size: 90%; line-height: 110%; z-index:90; position: relative; top: -1.5em; width: 6em; top:-0.15em; left: -3em; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"padding: 1px;\"><b>Maidenpool</b></span></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumbcaption\">The <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> and the location of Maidenpool\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Known_Lords_of_Maidenpool\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known Lords of Maidenpool</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_of_Maidenpool&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>At the start of the <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Conquest</a>, Lord Mooton allied himself with Lord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\">Darklyn</a> to fight <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon the Conqueror</a>. Both Lords died in the following <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_first_test\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s first test\">battle</a>, Lord Mooton's brother, <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Mooton\" title=\"Jon Mooton\">Jon Mooton</a>, yielded to Aegon and became the new Lord of Maidenpool. Lord Jon later fought for the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryens</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Field_of_Fire\" title=\"Field of Fire\">Field of Fire</a>, slaying men who tried to escape the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_Militant_uprising\" title=\"Faith Militant uprising\">Faith Militant uprising</a>, Lord Mooton slew Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Rupert_Falwell\" title=\"Rupert Falwell\">Rupert Falwell</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_at_the_Great_Fork\" title=\"Battle at the Great Fork\">battle at the Great Fork</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In his youth, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jonah_Mooton\" title=\"Jonah Mooton\">Jonah Mooton</a> was a friend of Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Saera_Targaryen\" title=\"Saera Targaryen\">Saera Targaryen</a>. When she disappeared in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_85_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">85&#160;AC</a> her father, King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>, asked Jonah to watch for her in Maidenpool.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>At the start of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Walys_Mooton\" title=\"Walys Mooton\">Walys Mooton</a> supported Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>'s claim to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>. In that effect, Lord Walys <a href=\"/index.php/Retaking_of_Rook%27s_Rest\" title=\"Retaking of Rook&#39;s Rest\">retook</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Rook%27s_Rest\" title=\"Rook&#39;s Rest\">Rook's Rest</a> for the <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a>. He was later slain in a failed attempt to kill King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a>'s dragon, <a href=\"/index.php/Sunfyre\" title=\"Sunfyre\">Sunfyre</a>. The older of his two brothers, <a href=\"/index.php/Manfryd_Mooton\" title=\"Manfryd Mooton\">Manfryd</a>, succeeded him as Lord of Maidenpool and continued to support the blacks.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord Manfryd hosted the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonrider\" title=\"Dragonrider\">dragonriders</a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Nettles\" title=\"Nettles\">Nettles</a> at Maidenpool for a time while the two were searching for Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond One-Eye</a> and his dragon, <a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a>. Lord Manfryd changed side and aligned his house with King Aegon and the <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">greens</a> after refusing to kill Nettles at Rhaenyra's behest.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the war, Lord Manfryd served as one of the seven initial council of <a href=\"/index.php/Regent\" title=\"Regent\">regents</a> for the King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>. Lord Mandfryd served until his own death due to <a href=\"/index.php/Illness\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Illness\">illness</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/134_AC\" title=\"134 AC\">134&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Rivers\" title=\"Brynden Rivers\">Bloodraven</a> marched on <a href=\"/index.php/Whitewalls\" title=\"Whitewalls\">Whitewalls</a> to quash the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"Second Blackfyre Rebellion\">Second Blackfyre Rebellion</a>, among the river lords who came in support was Lord Mooton.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_of_Maidenpool&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_of_Maidenpool&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/William_Mooton\" title=\"William Mooton\">William Mooton</a> supports King <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos72.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos72.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>According to a nameless traveller, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/William_Mooton\" title=\"William Mooton\">William Mooton</a> and his sons try to hunt <a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria_(direwolf)\" title=\"Nymeria (direwolf)\">a huge she-wolf</a> that had attacked some <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_of_Maidenpool&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Despite Maidenpool having been sacked three times during the war, Lord William still holds the town.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_of_Maidenpool&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a> arrives at Maidenpool and sets out at taking control of the town and fighting outlaws in the region while Lord William remains safely behind his walls.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup> Lord William agrees to betroth his eldest daughter and heir, <a href=\"/index.php/Eleanor_Mooton\" title=\"Eleanor Mooton\">Eleanor Mooton</a>, to Randyll's son and heir, <a href=\"/index.php/Dickon_Tarly\" title=\"Dickon Tarly\">Dickon Tarly</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_Lords_of_Maidenpool\">Known Lords of Maidenpool</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_of_Maidenpool&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known Lords of Maidenpool\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Lord Mooton at the start of the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_Conquest\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"War of Conquest\">War of Conquest</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Mooton\" title=\"Jon Mooton\">Jon Mooton</a>, his brother and successor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Lord Mooton, ruling during the reign of kings <a href=\"/index.php/Aenys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aenys I Targaryen\">Aenys I</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Lord Mooton, ruling during the early reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_20-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-20\">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_21-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-21\">&#91;21&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jonah_Mooton\" title=\"Jonah Mooton\">Jonah Mooton</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Walys_Mooton\" title=\"Walys Mooton\">Walys Mooton</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Manfryd_Mooton\" title=\"Manfryd Mooton\">Manfryd Mooton</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Lord Mooton, ruling in <a href=\"/index.php/212_AC\" t